 Poisoning due to tricyclic antidepressant (TCA) ingestion is both a common and serious emergency in Germany. Regarding the widespread activity of TCA, interference with many different organ systems occurs. Besides complications of cerebral and pulmonary function, cardiac arrhythmias are seen as a dangerous effect of TCA intoxication. The mechanisms of pathophysiology in organ damage following TCA intoxication are discussed and an overview on the specific therapy and detoxication is given.  
